# RapidAid Emergency SOS Page UI Design

## Purpose

The Emergency SOS Page is the core feature of RapidAid. It enables users to instantly request emergency assistance, share their live location, notify emergency contacts, and receive real-time updates on ambulance dispatch and hospital assignment.

## Page Layout

### Header

- 🚑 RapidAid Logo
- Dashboard
- Emergency Status
- Notifications
- Profile

---

## Emergency SOS Section

### Main Button

🚨 **EMERGENCY SOS**

- Large red circular button
- One-tap activation
- Long press (3 seconds) to prevent accidental activation

---

## Live Location

Display:

- Current GPS Coordinates
- Address
- Accuracy
- Last Updated Time

Buttons:

- Refresh Location
- Share Live Location

---

## Emergency Type

User selects one:

- 🚗 Road Accident
- ❤️ Cardiac Emergency
- 🩸 Severe Bleeding
- 🔥 Fire Accident
- 🤕 Injury
- 👶 Pregnancy Emergency
- 🫁 Breathing Problem
- ⚠ Other Emergency

---

## AI Emergency Assessment

The AI analyzes:

- Emergency Type
- User Medical Profile
- Live Location
- Nearby Hospitals
- Traffic Conditions

Outputs:

- Severity Level (Low, Medium, High, Critical)
- Recommended Hospital
- Estimated Ambulance Arrival Time

---

## Ambulance Status

Display:

- Ambulance Number
- Driver Name
- Current Status
- Distance
- ETA

Status Examples:

- Request Sent
- Accepted
- On the Way
- Reached Patient
- Patient Picked Up
- Reached Hospital

---

## Hospital Recommendation

Display:

- Hospital Name
- Distance
- Available ICU Beds
- Available Doctors
- Emergency Facilities

Button:

- View Hospital Details

---

## Emergency Contacts

Automatically notify:

- Family Member 1
- Family Member 2
- Guardian

Notification includes:

- Live Location
- Emergency Type
- Ambulance Status
- Hospital Assigned

---

## Live Map

Features:

- Patient Location
- Ambulance Location
- Hospital Location
- Route Navigation
- ETA Display

---

## Emergency Timeline

1. SOS Activated
2. GPS Captured
3. AI Analysis Completed
4. Ambulance Assigned
5. Hospital Selected
6. Family Notified
7. Ambulance Arrived
8. Patient Transported
9. Hospital Treatment Started

